xicologist and may require sedation, neuromuscular paralysis, intubation, and mechanical ventilation in addition to the other measures.', 'Synergism', 'Rimegepant, Eptinezumab, Dihydroergotamine, Ubrogepant, Ergotamine, Galcanezumab, Atogepant, Methysergide, Erenumab, Fremanezumab', NULL, 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/276314/', '[1] "Product Information. Lithobid (lithium)." Ciba-Geigy Pharmaceuticals  (2002):[2] Mills KC "Serotonin syndrome: A clinical update." Crit Care Clin 13 (1997):  763[3] Sobanski T, Bagli M, Laux G, Rao ML "Serotonin syndrome after lithium add-on medication to paroxetine." Pharmacopsychiatry 30 (1997):  106-7[4] Gardner DM, Lynd LD "Sumatriptan contraindications and the serotonin syndrome." Ann Pharmacother 32 (1998):  33-8[5] Mathew NT, Tietjen GE, Lucker C "Serotonin syndrome complicating migraine pharmacotherapy." Cephalalgia 16 (1996):  323-7[6] Martin TG "Serotonin syndrome." Ann Emerg Med 28 (1996):  520-6[7] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[8] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[9] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Canadian Product Information." O 0 (2015):', 1767369485);
